31/01/2023, 09:22 - Shivaraj Ghangale: def encrypt(text, key):
    rail = [['\n' for i in range(len(text))]
            for j in range(key)]
    dir_down = False
    row, col = 0, 0
    for char in text:
        if (row == 0) or (row == key - 1):
            dir_down = not dir_down
        rail[row][col] = char
        col += 1
        if dir_down:
            row += 1
        else:
            row -= 1
    result = []
    for i in range(key):
        for j in range(len(text)):
            if rail[i][j] != '\n':
                result.append(rail[i][j])
    return("".join(result))

def decrypt(cipher, key):
    rail = [['\n' for i in range(len(cipher))]
            for j in range(key)]
    dir_down = None
    row, col = 0, 0
    for i in range(len(cipher)):
        if row == 0:
            dir_down = True
        if row == key - 1:
            dir_down = False
        rail[row][col] = '*'
        col += 1
        if dir_down:
            row += 1
        else:
            row -= 1
    index = 0
    for i in range(key):
        for j in range(len(cipher)):
            if ((rail[i][j] == '*') and
               (index < len(cipher))):
                rail[i][j] = cipher[index]
                index += 1
    result = []
    row, col = 0, 0
    for i in range(len(cipher)):
        if row == 0:
            dir_down = True
        if row == key - 1:
            dir_down = False
        if rail[row][col] != '*':
            result.append(rail[row][col])
            col += 1
        if dir_down:
            row += 1
        else:
            row -= 1
    return("".join(result))

text = input("Enter the Text : ")
key = int(input("Enter the Key Size : "))
cipher = encrypt(text, key)
print("Encrypted Text : ", cipher)
plain = decrypt(cipher, key)
print("Decrypted Text : ", plain)

13/02/2023, 23:42 - Shivaraj Ghangale: import random
import math
def gcd(a, b):
"""
Calculates the greatest common divisor of two numbers using the
Euclidean algorithm
"""
while b != 0:
a, b = b, a % b
return a
def is_prime(num):
"""
Returns True if the number is prime, False otherwise
"""
if num < 2:
return False
for i in range(2, int(math.sqrt(num)) + 1):

if num % i == 0:
return False
return True
def generate_key_pair(p, q):
"""
Generates a public and private key pair based on two prime numbers
"""
if not (is_prime(p) and is_prime(q)):
raise ValueError("Both numbers must be prime")
elif p == q:
raise ValueError("p and q cannot be equal")
n = p * q
phi = (p - 1) * (q - 1)
e = random.randrange(1, phi)
g = gcd(e, phi)
while g != 1:
e = random.randrange(1, phi)
g = gcd(e, phi)
d = 0
k = 1
while (k * phi + 1) % e != 0:
k += 1
d = (k * phi + 1) // e
return ((e, n), (d, n))
def encrypt(plaintext, public_key):
"""
Encrypts the plaintext using the public key
"""
key, n = public_key
ciphertext = [(ord(char) ** key) % n for char in plaintext]
return ciphertext
def decrypt(ciphertext, private_key):
"""
Decrypts the ciphertext using the private key
"""
key, n = private_key
plaintext = [chr((char ** key) % n) for char in ciphertext]
return ''.join(plaintext)
if __name__ == '__main__':
p = int(input("Enter a prime number : "))
q = int(input("Enter another prime number : "))
public, private = generate_key_pair(p, q)
print("Your public key is ", public)
print("Your private key is ", private)
message = input("Enter a message to encrypt with your public key : ")
encrypted_message = encrypt(message, public)
print("Your encrypted message is : ")
print(''.join(map(lambda x: str(x), encrypted_message)))
print("Decrypting message with private key ", private)
print("Your message is : ")
print(decrypt(encrypted_message, private))

30/09/2021, 11:06 - Omkar Kc Friend: import java.util.*;

class Digits
{	
	public static void main (String args[])
	{
		int n;
		n=Integer.parseInt(args[0]);
		if(n<0)
		{
			System.out.println("Invalid data");
			
		}
		else
		{
			int digit,sum=0;
		    while(n!=0)
		    {
			   digit=n%10;
			   sum=sum+digit;
			   n=n/10;
		    }
		    System.out.println("Sum of digits is "+sum);
			
		}
	}
}

11/10/2021, 14:59 - Omkar Kc Friend: #include<stdio.h>

#define MAX 05

int QueueArray[MAX];
int front=-1;
int rear=-1;

int insert(int x)
{
    if(rear==MAX-1)
        printf("car centre  is full");
        return 0;
    if(front==-1)
        front=0;
    rear++;
    QueueArray[rear]=x;
    return 1;
}
int del()
{
    int x;
    if(front==-1)
        printf("car centre is empty");
        return -1;
    x=QueueArray[front];
    if(front==rear)
        rear=front=-1;
    else
        front++;
    return x;
}
int peek()
{
    if(front==-1)
        printf("car centre is empty");
        return -1;
   
    if(front==rear)
        rear=front=-1;
    
    return QueueArray[front];
}

int full()
{
    if(rear==MAX-1)
        return 1;
    else
        return -1;
}
int empty()
{
    if(front==-1)
        return 1;
    else
        return -1;
}
void display()
{
    int i=0;
    if(front==-1)
        printf("car centre  is empty");
    else
        for(i=front;i<=rear;i++)
            printf("%d",QueueArray[i]);
}
int main()
{
    int option,x,op;
    do
    {
        printf("****Choose an Option****\n");
        printf("1.Insert into the car centre\n");
        printf("2.Remove into the car centre\n");
        printf("3.Check the bookings\n");
        printf("4.dispaly\n");
        printf("5.Check Whether car centre is empty\n");
        printf("6.Check Whether car centre is full\n");
        printf("7.Exit\n");

        printf("Enter Your Option: \n");
        scanf("%d",&option);

        switch(option)
        {
            case 1:printf("Enter the number to be inserted into the car centre\n");
                scanf("%d",&x);
                op=insert(x);
                if(op=0)
                    printf("car not inserted\n");
            break;

            case 2:op=del();
                if(op==-1)
                    printf("car not remove\n");
                else
                    printf("%d",op);
                break;
            case 3:op=peek();
                if(op==-1)
                    printf("no bookings in car centre \n");
                else
                    printf("%d",op);
                break;
            case 4:display();
                break;
            case 5:if(front==-1)
                        printf("car centre is empty\n");
                    else
                        printf("car centre is not empty\n");
                    break;
            case 6:if(rear==MAX-1)
                        printf("car centre is full\n");
                    else
                        printf("car centre is not full\n");
                    break;
            case 7:break;
            default:printf("Invalid Option\n");
        }
    }
    while(option!=7);
    return 0;
}

26/10/2021, 15:10 - Omkar Kc Friend: //Write a program to implement constructor overloading 
//to calculate area of triangle and rectangle
import java.util.*;

class Rectangle
{
    int length, breadth;
  
    Rectangle(int l, int b) 
    { 
      length = l; 
      breadth = b; 
    } 
    Rectangle(int l) 
    { 
      length = l; 
      breadth = 20; 
    } 
    Rectangle() 
    { 
		length = 0; 
		breadth = 0; 
    }
    void readData()
    {
	   Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
	   System.out.println("Enter the Length and Breadth of Rectangle :");
	   length=sc.nextInt();
	   breadth=sc.nextInt();
    }   
    double getArea1() 
    { 
		return(length * breadth); 
    }
}
class Triangle
{
	int l,b;
	Triangle()
	{
		l=0;
		b=0;
	}
	Triangle(int l)
	{
		this.l=l;
		this.b=0;
	}
	Triangle(int l,int b)
	{
		this.l=l;
		this.b=b;
	}
	void readData()
    {
	   Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
	   System.out.println("Enter the Length and Breadth of Triangle :");
	   l=sc.nextInt();
	   b=sc.nextInt();
    } 
	double getArea2() 
    { 
      return(0.5*l * b); 
    }
}
public class Constructor
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
		Rectangle r = new Rectangle(); 
		r.readData();
		System.out.println("Area Of rectangle : " + r.getArea1());	  
		
		System.out.println();
	  
		Triangle t = new Triangle();
		
		t.readData();
		System.out.println("Area Of First Triangle : " + t.getArea2());

		
   }
}

08/11/2021, 09:48 - Omkar Kc Friend: #include<stdio.h>

#define MAX 10

int QueueArray[MAX];
int front=-1;
int rear=-1;
int count=0;

int insert(int x)
{
    if(count==MAX)
        return -1;
    if(front==-1)
        front++;
    rear++;
    QueueArray[rear]=x;
    count++;
    return 1;
}
int del()
{
    int x;
    if(count==0)
    {
    	printf("Queue is empty");
    	 return -1;
    	
    }
    	
       
    x=QueueArray[front];
    front++;
    
    if(front==MAX)
    {
    	front=0;
    }

    count--;
    if(count==0)
    {
    	front=rear=-1;
    }
    printf("%d is deleted",x);
    return x;
    
}


int full()
{
    if(count==MAX)
        return 1;
    else
        return -1;
}
int empty()
{
    if(count==0)
        return 1;
    else
        return -1;
}
void display()
{
    int i;
    if(count=0)
    {
    	printf("Queue is empty");
    }
    else
    {
    	printf("the contents of queue are\n");
    	i=front;
    	while(i!=rear+1)
    	{
    		printf("%d\n",QueueArray[i]);
    		i++;
    
	}
	
    }
    
}
int main()
{
    int option,x,op;
    do
    {
        printf("****Choose an Option****\n");
        printf("1.Insert Traffic Lights\n");
        printf("2.Remove Traffic Lights\n");
        printf("3.display Traffic Lights\n");
        printf("4.Check Whether queue is empty\n");
        printf("5.Check Whether queue is full\n");
        printf("6.Exit\n");

        printf("Enter Your Option: \n");
        scanf("%d",&option);

        switch(option)
        {
            case 1:printf("Enter the number to be inserted into the queue\n");
                scanf("%d",&x);
                op=insert(x);
                if(op=0)
                    printf("element not inserted\n");
                break;

            case 2:op=del();
                if(op==-1)
                    printf("element not remove\n");
                else
                    printf("%d deleted",op);
                break;
            
            case 3:display();
                    break;
            case 4:if(front==-1)
                        printf("queue is empty\n");
                    else
                        printf("queue is not empty\n");
                    break;
            case 5:if(rear==MAX-1)
                        printf("queue is full\n");
                    else
                        printf("queue is not full\n");
                    break;
            case 6:break;
            default:printf("Invalid Option\n");
        }
      //  getch();
    }
    while(option!=6);
    return 0;
}

08/11/2021, 10:53 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#define size 4
struct Node
{
  int data;
  struct Node *next;
};
typedef struct Node node;
node *head = NULL;

node *addNode()
{
  node *temp = malloc(sizeof(node));
  temp->next = NULL;
  return temp;
}
node *insertData(node *head, int value)
{

  node *temp;
  temp = addNode();
  temp->data = value;
  if (head == NULL)
    head = temp;
  else
 {
    node *p;
    p = head;
    while (p->next != NULL)
    {
      p = p->next;
    }
    p->next = temp;
  } 

return head;
}
node *insertAtBeginning(node *head, int value)
{
  node *temp = addNode();
  temp->data = value;
  temp->next = head;
  head = temp;
  return head;
}
 void insertAtEnd(node *head,int value)
{
  node *temp=addNode();
  node *last=head;
  temp->data=value;
  if(head==NULL){
    head=temp;
    return;
  }
while(last->next!=NULL){
    last=last->next;
  }
  last->next=temp;
  return;

}

void deleteFromEnd(node *head)
{
   node *temp= head;
   while(temp->next->next!=NULL){
     temp=temp->next;
   }
   temp->next=NULL;
 return;
}

void printList(node *head)
{
  node *temp = head;
  if (temp == NULL)
    printf("Nothing To Print:\n");
  else
  {
 printf("Printing list:\n");
    while (temp != NULL)
    {
      printf("%d->", temp->data);
      temp = temp->next;
    }
  }
}

int main(int argc, char const *argv[])
{
  int ch, value;

  while (1)
  {
    printf("\n1.Enter the student \n2.Display the list in linked manner\n3.Insert student at beginning\n4.Insert student at end\n5.Delete From End \n6.Quit\n");
printf("\nEnter your choice:");
    scanf("%d", &ch);

    switch (ch)
    {
    case 1:
 printf("Enter the student:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      head = insertData(head, value);

      break;
    case 2:
      printList(head);
      break;
    case 3:
      printf("Enter a student at Begginning:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      head = insertAtBeginning(head, value);
      break;
case 4:
      printf("Enter a student at End:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      insertAtEnd(head,value);
      break;
     case 5:
     deleteFromEnd(head);
     break;
    case 0:
      return 0;
      break;
  default:
      break;
    }
  }

  //printf("%d",head);
  // printList(head);
  return 0;
}

09/11/2021, 11:26 - Omkar Kc Friend: /*Write a program to compute Simple Interest 
and Compound interest.
multilevel inheritance


Create 2 classes.
Base -> Data
Derieved 1 ->Simple
Derieved 2 -> Compound
Display the result.     */


import java.util .*;
class Base
{
	double p, n, r,si,ci;
	public void read()
	{
		Scanner s=new Scanner (System. in);
        System.out.println("Enter the amount:");
        p=s.nextDouble( );
        System. out. println("Enter the No.of years:");
        n=s.nextDouble( );
        System. out. println("Enter the Rate of  interest");
        r=s.nextDouble( );
		System.out. println("Amount="+p );
        System. out. println("No. of years="+n);
        System. out. println("Rate of interest="+r);
	}
}
class SubClass extends Base
{
	public void display()
	{
		super.read();
		si=(p*n*r)/100;
		System.out.println("Simple Interest="+si);
	}
}
class SubClass2 extends SubClass
{
	public void display()
	{
		super.display();
		ci=p*Math.pow(1.0+r/100.0,n)-p;
		System.out. println("Compound Interest="+ci);
	}
}


class Inheritance1
{
    public static void main (String args [ ])
    {
		Base b=new Base();
		SubClass s1=new SubClass();
        SubClass2 s2=new SubClass2();
        
		s2.display();

    }
}

15/11/2021, 15:30 - Omkar Kc Friend: //WAP to implement the Koch Curve. 
#include<stdio.h> 
#include<graphics.h> 
#include<math.h> 
void koch(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, int i) 
{ 
	float angle = 60*M_PI/180; 
	int x3 = (2*x1+x2)/3; 
	int y3 = (2*y1+y2)/3; 
	int x4 = (x1+2*x2)/3; 
	int y4 = (y1+2*y2)/3; 
	int x = x3 + (x4-x3)*cos(angle)+(y4-y3)*sin(angle); 
	int y = y3 - (x4-x3)*sin(angle)+(y4-y3)*cos(angle); 
	if(i > 0) 
	{ 
	  	koch(x1, y1, x3, y3, i-1); 
	  	koch(x3, y3, x, y, i-1); 
	  	koch(x, y, x4, y4, i-1); 
	  	koch(x4, y4, x2, y2,i-1); 
	  	setcolor(6); 
	} 
	else 
	{ 
	  	line(x1, y1, x3, y3); 
	  	line(x3, y3, x, y); 
	  	line(x, y, x4, y4); 
	  	line(x4, y4, x2, y2); 
	} 
	delay(10); 
} 
int main() 
{ 
	int gd = DETECT, gm; 
	initgraph(&gd, &gm, "C:\\TC\\BGI"); 
	int x1 , y1  , x2 , y2 ; 
	printf("\nEnter the Value of x1 and y1 :"); 
	scanf("%d%d",&x1,&y1); 
	printf("\nEnter the Value of x2 and y2 :"); 
	scanf("%d%d",&x2,&y2); 
	koch(x1, y1, x2, y2, 4); 
	getch(); 
	return 0; 
}

16/11/2021, 11:22 - Omkar Kc Friend: import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

abstract class Base
{
	double pi=3.14;
	double x,y,r;
	
	abstract double compute_area();
	
}
class Circle extends Base
{
	double compute_area()
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter the radius of Circle ");
		r=sc.nextDouble();
		return pi*r*r;
	}
}
class Rectangle extends Base
{
	double compute_area()
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter the Length and Breadth of Rectangle ");
		x=sc.nextDouble();
		y=sc.nextDouble();
		return x*y;
	}
}


class AbstractDemo
{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{
		
		Rectangle t=new Rectangle();
		Circle c = new Circle();
		
		System.out.println("Area of Rectangle is "+t.compute_area());
		System.out.println("Area of Circle is "+c.compute_area());
		
	}
}

16/11/2021, 11:22 - Omkar Kc Friend: // To implement 2D Transformation: Translation, 
// Rotation, Scaling, Reflection, Shear
#include<iostream>
#include<graphics.h>
#include<math.h>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int gd=DETECT,gm,s;
    initgraph(&gd,&gm,(char*)"");
    cout<<"1.Translation\n2.Rotation\n3.Scaling\n4.Reflection\n5.Shearing   "<<endl;
    cout<<"Selection:";
    cin>>s;
    switch(s)
        {
        case 1:
            {   int x1=200,y1=150,x2=300,y2=250;
                int tx=50,ty=50;
                cout<<"Rectangle before translation"<<endl;
                setcolor(3);
                rectangle(x1,y1,x2,y2);
                setcolor(4);
                cout<<"Rectangle after translation"<<endl;
                rectangle(x1+tx,y1+ty,x2+tx,y2+ty);
                getch();
                break;
            }
        case 2:
            {  long x1=200,y1=200,x2=300,y2=300;
                double a;
                cout<<"Rectangle with rotation"<<endl;
                setcolor(3);
                rectangle(x1,y1,x2,y2);
                cout<<"Angle of rotation:";
                cin>>a;
                a=(a*3.14)/180;
                long xr=x1+((x2-x1)*cos(a)-(y2-y1)*sin(a));
                long yr=y1+((x2-x1)*sin(a)+(y2-y1)*cos(a));
                setcolor(2);
                rectangle(x1,y1,xr,yr);
                getch();
                break;
}
        case 3:
            {
                int x1=30,y1=30,x2=70,y2=70,y=2,x=2;
                cout<<"Before scaling"<<endl;
                setcolor(3);
                rectangle(x1,y1,x2,y2);
                cout<<"After scaling"<<endl;
                setcolor(10);
                rectangle(x1*x,y1*y,x2*x,y2*y);
                getch();
                break;
}
        case 4:
            {
                 int x1=200,y1=300,x2=500,y2=300,x3=350,y3=400;
                 cout<<"triangle before reflection"<<endl;
                 setcolor(3);
                 line(x1,y1,x2,y2);
                 line(x1,y1,x3,y3);
                 line(x2,y2,x3,y3);
cout<<"triangle after reflection"<<endl;
                 setcolor(5);
                 line(x1,-y1+500,x2,-y2+500);
                 line(x1,-y1+500,x3,-y3+500);
                 line(x2,-y2+500,x3,-y3+500);
                 getch();
                 break;
}
        case 5:
        {
  int x1=300,y1=100,x2=400,y2=100,x3=300,y3=200,x4=400,y4=200,shx=1;
             cout<<"Before shearing of rectangle"<<endl;
             setcolor(3);
             line(x1,y1,x2,y2);
             line(x1,y1,x3,y3);
             line(x3,y3,x4,y4);
             line(x2,y2,x4,y4);
             cout<<"After shearing of rectangle"<<endl;
             x1=x1+shx*y1;
             x2=x2+shx*y2;
             x3=x3+shx*y3;
             x4=x4+shx*y4;
             setcolor(13);
             line(x1,y1,x2,y2);
             line(x1,y1,x3,y3);
             line(x3,y3,x4,y4);
             line(x2,y2,x4,y4);
getch();
}
default:
          {
            cout<<"Invalid Selection"<<endl;
            break;
          }
        }
closegraph();
    return 0;
}

15/12/2021, 13:11 - Shivaraj Ghangale: Implement Linear Queue using Linked list
 A car wash center washing cars 
1)Take the number of the car. 
2)Check the bookings. If available, insert the car in the car center 
for washing.
3)Cars will be washed out and delivered as per first come first 
out basis.
4) Display the total number of cars available in the center for 
washing.
15/12/2021, 13:11 - Omkar Kc Friend: haa hai ye
15/12/2021, 13:12 - Shivaraj Ghangale: Bhej de
15/12/2021, 13:14 - Shivaraj Ghangale: Bhej na pls
15/12/2021, 13:14 - Shivaraj Ghangale: Mere bhen ka he
15/12/2021, 13:19 - Omkar Kc Friend: /*Batch (A1B1)

Aim : Implement Linear Queue ADT using array.
Problem Statement: A car wash center allows max 05 cars for washing in a day.
1.	Take the number of the car. 92.	Check the bookings. If available, insert the car in the car center for washing.
3.	Cars will be washed out and delivered as per first come first out basis.
4.	Display the total number of cars available in the center for washing.        */

#include <stdio.h>
#define MAX 5

void insert();
void delete();
void display();
int queue_array[MAX];
int rear = - 1;
int front = - 1;
void main()
{
int choice;
do
{
printf("\n1.Insert car in car washing center \n");
printf("2.deliver washed  car \n");
printf("3.total number of cars present  in center \n");
printf("4.exit \n");
printf("\nEnter your choice : ");
scanf("%d", &choice);
switch (choice)
{
  case 1:
  insert();
  break;
  
  case 2:
  delete();
  break;

  case 3:
  display();
  break;
  
  case 4:printf("\nexit");
  break;
  
  default:
  printf("\nWrong choice \n");
}
}
while (choice!=4);
}


void insert()
{
int add_item;
if (rear == MAX - 1)
printf("\nbooking is full \n");
else
{
if (front == - 1)
front = 0;
printf("\nno.of car to insert in car washing center : ");
scanf("%d", &add_item);
rear = rear + 1;
queue_array[rear] = add_item;
}
}
void delete()
{
if (front == - 1 || front > rear)
{
printf("\nno of cars present in carwashing center \n");
return ;
}
else
{
printf("\ndelivered car no.is : %d\n", queue_array[front]);
front = front + 1;
}
}
void display()
{
int i;
if (front == - 1)
printf("\ncarwashing center is empty \n");
else
{
printf("\ntotal cars present in carwashing center : \n");
for (i = front; i <= rear; i++)
printf("%d ", queue_array[i]);
printf("\n");
}
}

15/12/2021, 13:28 - Omkar Kc Friend: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
typedef struct node
{
	int data;
	struct node *next;
}node;

typedef struct LL
{
	node *start;
}LL;

void display(LL *l)
{
	node *p;
	if(l->start==NULL)
	{
		printf("\n List is empty");
	}
	else
	{
		p=l->start;
		while(p!=NULL)
		{
			printf("\n %d",p->data);
			p=p->next;
		}
	}
}

void enqueue(LL *l,int x)
{
	node *newrec,*p;;
	newrec=(node*)malloc(sizeof(node));
	newrec->data=x;
	newrec->next=NULL;
	if(l->start==NULL)
	{
		l->start=newrec;
	}
	else
	{
		p=l->start;
		while(p->next!=NULL)
		{
			p=p->next;
		}
		p->next=newrec;
	}
}

void dequeue(LL *l,int x)
{
	node *p;
	if(l->start==NULL)
	{
		printf("\n Deletion not possible");
	}
	else
	{
		p=l->start;
		l->start=l->start->next;
		p->next=NULL;
		free(p);
	}
}


int main()
{
	int ch,x;
	LL l;
	l.start=NULL;
	while(1)
	{
		printf("\nMenu:\n1-Enqueue\n2-Dequeue\n3-Display\n4-Exit\nEnter choice =");
		scanf("%d",&ch);
		if(ch==4)
		break;
		switch(ch)
		{
			case 1:
				{
					printf("Enter element to be inserted =\n");
					scanf("%d",&x);
					enqueue(&l,x);
					display(&l);
				}
				break;
			case 2:
				{
					dequeue(&l,x);
					display(&l);
				}
				break;
			case 3:
				{
					display(&l);
				}
				break;
			default:
				{
					printf("Invalid Choice\n");
				}
		}
	}
	return 0;
}

from array import *

def Addition(a):
    sum = 0
    for i in a:
        sum = sum + i
    return (sum)

n = int(input("Enter a Array Size : "))
a = array('i',[])
print("Enter array elements = ")

for i in range(n):
    Num = int(input())
    a.insert(i,Num)

print(a)
ans = Addition(a)

print('Sum of the array is ', ans)
#b = sorted(a)

27/09/2021, 12:31 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#define size 5
#define MAX 5

int stack[size];

struct stack {
   int arr[MAX];
   int top;
};
 
void init_stk(struct stack *st) {
   st->top = -1;
}
 
void push(struct stack *st, int num) {
   if (st->top == size - 1) {
      printf("\nStack overflow(i.e., stack full).");
      return;
   }
   st->top++;
   st->arr[st->top] = num;
}
 
int pop(struct stack *st) {
   int num;
   if (st->top == -1) {
      printf("\nStack underflow(i.e., stack empty).");
      return NULL;
   }
   num = st->arr[st->top];
   st->top--;
   return num;
}
 
void display(struct stack *st) {
   int i;
   for (i = st->top; i >= 0; i--)
      printf("\n%d", st->arr[i]+5);
}
 
int main() {
   int element, opt, val;
   struct stack ptr;
   init_stk(&ptr);
   printf("\nTransfer chairs from computer lab to seminar hall");
   while (1) {
      printf("\n1.PUSH");
      printf("\n2.DISPLAY");
      printf("\n3.POP");
      printf("\n4.QUIT");
      printf("\n");
      printf("\nEnter your option : ");
      scanf("%d", &opt);
      switch (opt) {
      case 1:
           printf("\nInitially there are 5 Chair Present");
         printf("\nEnter number of chairs to be inserted in a bunch:");
         scanf("%d", &val);
         push(&ptr, val);
         break;
      case 2:
          printf("\nThe current stack elements are:");
         display(&ptr);
         break;      
      case 3:
         element = pop(&ptr);
         printf("\nThe element popped from stack is : %d", element);
         break;
      case 4:
         exit(0);
      default:
         printf("\nEnter correct option!Try again.");
      }
   }
   return (0);
}

    @Override                                                                                                                      
    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {                                                                                   
        if (e.getSource() == button1) {                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                   
            hj=field1.getText();                                                                                                   
            jh= passwordField.getText();                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                   
            if (hj.length()>15){                                                                                                   
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"Enter less than 15","warning",JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);                    
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
            if (hj.isEmpty() || jh.isBlank()){                                                                                     
                // JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"yes perfect","right",JOptionPane.INFORMATION_MESSAGE);                      
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Enter username/password please", "error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);         
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
            else if (hj.startsWith(ko[1]) || hj.startsWith(ko[0]) || hj.startsWith(ko[2]) || hj.startsWith(ko[3]) || hj.startsWith(
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Enter string not integer", "error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);               
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
            else if (jh.length()<8){                                                                                               
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"password should be of 8 characters","warning",JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);    
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
            else {                                                                                                                 
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"login successful :)","login",JOptionPane.INFORMATION_MESSAGE);                 
                New nt=new New();                                                                                                  
                //frame.dispose();                                                                                                 
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
        }                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                   
        if (e.getSource()==button3){                                                                                               
            hj=field1.getText();                                                                                                   
            jh= passwordField.getText();                                                                                           
            if (hj!=" " || jh!=" "){                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                   
                field1.setText(" ");                                                                                               
                passwordField.setText(" ");                                                                                        
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                   
        }                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                   
        if (e.getSource()==button2){                                                                                               
            Sig bw=new Sig();                                                                                                      
            JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"please sign_up","signup",JOptionPane.PLAIN_MESSAGE);                               
            frame.dispose();                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                   
        }                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                   
        if (e.getSource() == showPassword)                                                                                         
        {                                                                                                                          
            if (showPassword.isSelected())                                                                                         
            {                                                                                                                      
                passwordField.setEchoChar((char)0);                                                                                
            }                                                                                                                      
            else                                                                                                                   
            {                                                                                                                      
                passwordField.setEchoChar('*');                                                                                    
            }                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                   
        }                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                   
    }

13/12/2021, 20:40 - Janmejay Mayurya: #include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
#include<graphics.h>  
void drawline(int x0, int y0, int x1, int y1)  
{  
    int dx, dy, p, x, y;  
    dx=x1-x0;  
    dy=y1-y0;  
    x=x0;  
    y=y0;  
    p=2*dy-dx;  
    while(x<x1)  
    {  
        if(p>=0)  
        {  
            putpixel(x,y,7);  
            y=y+1;  
            p=p+2*dy-2*dx;  
        }  
        else  
        {  
            putpixel(x,y,7);  
            p=p+2*dy;}  
            x=x+1;  
        }  
}  
int main()  
{  
    int gdriver=DETECT, gmode, error, x0, y0, x1, y1;  
    initgraph(&gdriver, &gmode, "c:\\turboc3\\bgi");  
    printf("Co-ordinates of first point: ");  
    scanf("%d%d", &x0, &y0);  
    printf("Co-ordinates of second point: ");  
    scanf("%d%d", &x1, &y1);  
    drawline(x0, y0, x1, y1);
    getch();
    return 0;
}

06/10/2022, 21:23 - Janmejay Mayurya: Results
This is some output our project .
Conclusion
We can conclude that the capabilities of the whatsapp application and the power of the python programming language in implementing our data analysis intended, cannot be overemphasized.
The system was done with python, and the python libraries that were implemented includes, streamlit, Pandas, Re, Matplotlib, URL extract, etc.
Finally results that we intended were obtained. The future of our project is that it is mainly useful for organizers, and user will get to know who is more and least active in the group. Depending on that user can take decisions.
On a serious note this system has the ability to analyse any whatsapp group or individual data input into it.

22/05/2022, 16:11 - SATYAM Friend: *VIEW SERIALIZABLE*                                                                                                                                                                      .                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        1.We know that a serial schedule never leaves the database in
inconsistent state because there are no concurrent
transactions execution.

2.However a non-serial schedule can leave the database in
inconsistent state because there are multiple transactions
running concurrently.

3.By checking that a given non-serial schedule is view
serializable, we make sure that it is a consistent schedule..

22/05/2022, 16:28 - SATYAM Friend: *CONFLIC SERIALIZABLE*                                                                          .                                                                                                                                                           .                                                                                                                                                                                                   1.Conflict Serializability is one of the type of Serializability,
which can be used to check whether a non-serial schedule is
conflict serializable or not.

2.A schedule is called conflict serializable if we can convert it
into a serial schedule after swapping its non-conflicting
operations.

3.A conflict Serializability arises when one of the instruction is
a write operation.                                                                                                                                                                                                               .                                                                                                                                                                                                                     4.Conflict serializability defines two instructions of two
different transactions accessing the same data item to
perform a read/write operation.

5. It deals with detecting the instructions that are conflicting in
any way and specifying the order in which the instructions
should execute in case there is any conflict.

22/05/2022, 18:03 - SATYAM Friend: Deadlock is a state of a database system having two or more transactions, when each transaction is waiting for a data item that is being locked by some other transaction. A deadlock can be indicated by a cycle in the wait-for-graph. 

There are three classical approaches for deadlock handling, namely −

Deadlock prevention.
Deadlock avoidance.
Deadlock detection and removal.

All of the three approaches can be incorporated in both a centralized and a distributed database system.

Deadlock Prevention

1.Deadlock prevention method is suitable for a large database. If the resources are allocated in such a way that deadlock never occurs, then the deadlock can be prevented.
2.The Database management system analyzes the operations of the transaction whether they can create a deadlock situation or not. If they do, then the DBMS never allowed that transaction to be executed.

Deadlock Avoidance

1.When a database is stuck in a deadlock state, then it is better to avoid the database rather than aborting or restating the database. This is a waste of time and resource.
2.Deadlock avoidance mechanism is used to detect any deadlock situation in advance. A method like "wait for graph" is used for detecting the deadlock situation but this method is suitable only for the smaller database. For the larger database, deadlock prevention method can be used.

Deadlock Detection
In a database, when a transaction waits indefinitely to obtain a lock, then the DBMS should detect whether the transaction is involved in a deadlock or not. The lock manager maintains a Wait for the graph to detect the deadlock cycle in the database.
22/05/2022, 21:23 - SATYAM Friend: *UPDATED*                                                                                                                                                                                                 .                                                                                                                                                                        Deadlock is a state of a database system having two or more transactions, when each transaction is waiting for a data item that is being locked by some other transaction. A deadlock can be indicated by a cycle in the wait-for-graph. 

There are three classical approaches for deadlock handling, namely −

Deadlock prevention.
Deadlock avoidance.
Deadlock detection and removal.

All of the three approaches can be incorporated in both a centralized and a distributed database system.

Deadlock Prevention

1.Deadlock prevention method is suitable for a large database. If the resources are allocated in such a way that deadlock never occurs, then the deadlock can be prevented.
2.The Database management system analyzes the operations of the transaction whether they can create a deadlock situation or not. If they do, then the DBMS never allowed that transaction to be executed.

Deadlock Avoidance

1.When a database is stuck in a deadlock state, then it is better to avoid the database rather than aborting or restating the database. This is a waste of time and resource.
2.Deadlock avoidance mechanism is used to detect any deadlock situation in advance. A method like "wait for graph" is used for detecting the deadlock situation but this method is suitable only for the smaller database. For the larger database, deadlock prevention method can be used.                                                                                                     .                                                                                                                                                                                         Deadlock Detection and Recovery                                                                                                                                          We can allow system to enter a deadlock state and then we can detect such state by deadlock detection techniques and try to recover from deadlock state by using and deadlock recovery scheme.

✨ *About E-Cell ?!*🌟

👉🏻E-Cell  gives you a platform where you can start your entrepreneurial journey while balancing your college life.

👉🏻 It's a committee where the members get to work on projects and are using new technologies. 

👉🏻 Students who wish to do and also promote their Start-ups, are guided through their entrepreneurship journey.

👉🏻 Members get opportunity to work different projects as freelancers based on one's expertise in the subject.

👉🏻 Student gets to work with the Seniors and Mentors of E-Cell.

👉🏻 Works in latest tech domains and experiences team strength efforts.

👉🏻If you have keen interest in learning new technical skills.

16/11/2022, 17:27 - SATYAM Friend: TCS mod 1  all sem question (2018-2022)


1. (a) Design a Finite State Machine to determine whether ternary number (base 3)
is divisible 5.(nov18)

2. 
(a) Convert (0+1 )(10)*(0+1) into NFA with E-moves and obtain DFA.
(b) Construct Moore and Mealy Machine to convert each occurrence of 100 by 101. (nov18)(nov19)

3. short note (d) Moore and Mealy Machine(nov 18)

4. (a) Differentiate DFA and NFA.
(b) Design a DFA to accept string of 0's and I 's ending with the string 100.(may19kt)E

5.
(a) Design NFA for recognizing the strings that end in "aa" over  Σ={a,b} & convert
above NFA to DFA.
(b) Design moore m/c for following:-
If input ends in '101 ' then output should be A, if input ends in '110' output should be
B, otherwise output should be C and convert it into mealy m/c. (may19kt)

6.Compare and Contrast Moore and Mealy Machine(may22kt)
7.Give the Moore and Mealy machine for the following processes :
"For input from ( 0 + 1 )* M inputs ends in 101 , output x ; if input ends in
110 , output y ; otherwise output z " (may22kt)
8.Obtain DE4 to accept strings ofOS and 1 with even no. ofOS and even no. of (may22kt)
9.Convert the following RE to €- NFA and then convert it to DFA :
    R=((0+1)*10+(00)*(11)*)* (may22kt)

01/12/2022, 22:16 - SATYAM Friend: Create an HTML page which will divide a page in two horizontal fragments using
frameset tag, each frame should have different background color & different heading

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Frame Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <frameset cols="50%,50%">
        <frame src="frame1.html" />
        <frame src="frame2.html" />
    </frameset>
</body>
</html>

 frame1.html
 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Frame 1</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="red">
    <h1>Frame 1 Heading</h1>
</body>
</html>

<html>
<head>
    <title>Employee Details</title>
</head>
<body>
    <form action="employee.php" method="POST">
        <label>Name</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="name"/><br><br>
        <label>Address</label><br>
        <textarea name="address" cols="30" rows="5"></textarea><br><br>
        <label>Gender</label><br>
        <select name="gender">
            <option value="male">Male</option>
            <option value="female">Female</option>
        </select><br><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit"/>
    </form>
</body>
</html>

15/12/2022, 20:31 - Om Friend: Dear Students,
*Bureau of Indian Standards*(BIS- Ministry of Consumer affairs, food and distribution, Govt of India) is celebrating its foundation day on 6th Jan’23. In this regards they are conducting campaigning. 
We have our BIS Standard Club at our college which was formed in Oct’22.
This event will bring different aspect of practical learning to your day to day activity.
I therefore suggest you to participate actively in this program.
Be careful while you fill the form as it requires your Bank details for direct money transfer from Govt.
All the students  will be provided T-Shirts, caps, Badges and Certificates. The volunteers will be given an honorarium of Rs. 1 ,500/- subject to submission of min 25 nos. of duly filled feedback forms/entries on mobile app. of the household visited
Before the event all the registered students will be called at the campus to collect the T-shirt and Cap. Event description will be shared by BIS officials on the same day. Date and time will be communicated to you well in advance. 
Since this will be a week long program so the campaign can be conducted on either 5th or 6th or 7th or 8th Dec’22. 
*Most Important :If you are very sure that you will attend the event then only fill it.*
You may give your confirmation by filling up below registration form:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeHnnw5-vDDDiVi2SaF6wii_cPfDTAXk67VIWtnPF_bpL9y7g/viewform?usp=pp_url

Instructions:
•	In the club member option, mention No.
•	Leave the club serial no question.
Thank you.
Dr Ravi Prakash, Mentor, BIS Standard Club
KCCEMSR, Thane.

°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°°
✨ *About CDC ?!*🌟

👉🏻CDC is a Core committee which prepares an overall comprehensive development plan of the college regarding academic, administrative and infrastructural growth, and enable college to foster excellence in curricular, co-curricular and extracurricular activities.

✨ Roles CDC :-

👉🏻 Identify companies for each branches which might provide some benefit to them

👉🏻 Should have information and should be aware about the college events happening and should make sure all the events are taking place with due permission (Student)

👉🏻 Should organize workshops and seminars according to students interest and pooling of creative ideas (Student)

01/02/2023, 23:29 - Omkar Kc Friend: Say we are given keys in the range 0 to 999, and have a hash table of size 10. In this case, a possible hash function might simply divide the key value by 100. Thus, all keys in the range 0 to 99 would hash to slot 0, keys 100 to 199 would hash to slot 1, and so on.

01/02/2023, 23:42 - Omkar Kc Friend: The two methods of operation in Authentication Header (AH) are:

Transport mode: used to protect the integrity and authenticity of an IP datagram, but not the confidentiality.
Tunnel mode: used to protect the entire inner IP datagram, including confidentiality.
The two methods of operation in Encapsulating Security Payload (ESP) are:

Transport mode: used to protect the confidentiality, integrity, and authenticity of an IP datagram.
Tunnel mode: used to protect the entire inner IP datagram, including confidentiality, integrity, and authenticity.

02/02/2023, 00:13 - Janmejay Mayurya: The two methods of operation in Authentication Header (AH) are:

Transport Mode: In this mode, AH is used to provide integrity and authentication for upper-layer protocols and for IP datagrams, but it does not provide confidentiality.

Tunnel Mode: In this mode, AH is used to provide the same level of protection as transport mode, but for IP packets that have been encapsulated (i.e., "tunneled"). This mode is commonly used to protect VPN connections

*Excelssior Education Society's*  -
*K. C. College of Engineering and Management Studies and Research, Kopri, Thane (E)*.

*Value Added Cell in association with IQAC, CSI & IETE-ISF*

 *Introduction to IoT certified by CISCO*

                                            
*Objectives*: 
•The aim of this VAC is to introduce the participants to the amazing world of IoT and IOT’s fascinating applications. 
•To design and develop applications to solve real world problems.
•To implement the mini-projects using hardware and software

Who can attend:- 
*Students of All SE and TE Students*

19/09/2020, 19:07 - Shivaraj Ghangale: *"अधिक मास"*
१६० वर्षांनी आला दुर्मिळ संयोग
एक माळ जप केल्याने शंभर पट फलप्राप्ती
*"दोन अश्विन मास असलेला दुर्मिळ अधिक मास योग"*

१६० वर्षानी लीप ईयर आणि अश्विन अधिक मास एकाच वर्षात
‌१८६०मध्ये असा अधिक मास आला होता त्यानंतर असा सुयोग आता आलेला आहे

*"अधिक मासा चा खास मंत्र""*.

*"ओम नमो भगवते वासुदेवाय नमः"*
  *हा मंत्र देईल अक्षय पुण्य फळ.*

१८ सप्टेंबर ते १६ ऑक्टोंबर पर्यंत अधिक मास आहे.
अधिक मासाचे अधिष्ठाता श्री भगवान विष्णू आहेत. त्यामुळे पूर्ण अधिक मास श्रीविष्णू देवतेचा मंत्रजप केल्यामुळे विशेष लाभ होतो.
     
असे मानले जाते की जो कोणी भक्त म्हणजेच साधक श्री विष्णू मंत्राचा जप करतो त्या भक्ताला म्हणजेच साधकाला  *श्री भगवान विष्णु स्वतःहून आशीर्वाद देतात, त्यांच्या पापांचे शमन करतात, आणि विशेष महत्त्व म्हणजे त्यांच्या समस्त इच्छा पूर्ण करतात*.
अशी मान्यता आहे की अधिक मासामध्ये श्री भगवान विष्णूच्या मंत्र जपा चे फळ १०० पटीने मिळते.
म्हणून ज्या भक्ताला
*ओम नमो भगवते वासुदेवाय नमः*
ह्या जपाची रोज एक माळ सकाळी उठल्यापासून रात्री झोपेपर्यंत केव्हा पण करण्याची इच्छा असेल त्या भक्तांनी ह्या संधीचा अवश्य लाभ घ्यावा.
स्वतःही ह्या संधीचा लाभ घ्यावा व इतरांना पण सांगावे. स्वतः करून इतरांना जो कोणी करायला सांगेल त्यांना श्री विष्णू भगवंता कडून अगणित फलप्राप्ती होईल.

वासुदेव हंसते हुए बोले : हे पार्थ , जो आप से नहीं होगा वह में करुंगा। 
पार्थ ने कहा : प्रभु ऐसा क्या है जो मैं नहीं कर सकता ??

वासुदेव फिर हंसे और बोले : जिस अस्थिर , विचलित , हिलते हुए पानी में तुम मछली का निशाना साधोगे , उस विचलित "पानी" को स्थिर "मैं" रखुंगा !!

कहने का तात्पर्य यह है कि आप चाहे कितने ही निपुण क्यूँ ना हो , कितने ही बुद्धिमान क्यूँ ना हो , कितने ही महान एवं विवेकपूर्ण क्यूँ ना हो , लेकिन आप स्वंय हरेक परिस्थिति के उपर पूर्ण नियंत्रण नहीँ रख सकते .... आप सिर्फ अपना प्रयास कर सकते हैं , लेकिन उसकी भी एक सीमा है।

और जो उस सीमा से आगे की बागडोर संभालता है उसी का नाम "भगवान" है ....!!

30/08/2021, 14:48 - Om Friend: #include <stdio.h>    //write a c program to swap adjacent of a one dimensional array.

int main()
{
    
    int t;
    int i;
    int temp;

    
    printf("How many numbers you want to enter : ");
    scanf("%d", &t);

    
    int a[t];

    
    for (i = 0; i < t; i++)
    {
        printf("Enter element for position %d : ", i + 1);
        scanf("%d", &a[i]);
    }

    
    printf("Array entered : \n");
    for (i = 0; i < t; i++)
    {
        printf("%d ", a[i]);
    }

    
    for (i = 0; i < t; i += 2)
    {
        
        if (i + 1 == t)
        {
            break;
        }

        
        temp = a[i];
        a[i] = a[i + 1];
        a[i + 1] = temp;
    }

    
    printf("\nArray after reversing is done : \n");
    for (i = 0; i < t; i++)
    {
        printf("%d ", a[i]);
    }
}

06/09/2021, 11:21 - Om Friend: #include<stdio.h>

int main()
{
    //1
    int i;
    int firstNumber,secondNumber;

    //2
    int firstDivisorSum = 0;
    int secondDivisorSum = 0;

    //3
    printf("Enter two numbers to check if Amicable or not : ");
    scanf("%d %d",&firstNumber,&secondNumber);

    //4
    for(int i=1;i<firstNumber;i++){
    //5
        if(firstNumber % i == 0){
            firstDivisorSum = firstDivisorSum + i;
        }
    }

    //6
    for(int i=1;i<secondNumber;i++){
        if(secondNumber % i == 0){
            secondDivisorSum = secondDivisorSum + i;
        }
    }

    //7
    if((firstNumber == secondDivisorSum) && (secondNumber == firstDivisorSum)){
        printf("%d and %d are Amicable numbers\n",firstNumber,secondNumber);
    }else{
        printf("%d and %d are not Amicable numbers\n",firstNumber,secondNumber);
    }

}

#include <graphics.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <dos.h>
 
void main( )
{
float x,y,x1,y1,x2,y2,dx,dy,step;
int i,gd=DETECT,gm;
 
initgraph(&gd,&gm,"c:\\turboc3\\bgi");
 
printf("Enter the value of x1 and y1 : ");
scanf("%f%f",&x1,&y1);
printf("Enter the value of x2 and y2: ");
scanf("%f%f",&x2,&y2);
 
dx=abs(x2-x1);
dy=abs(y2-y1);
 
if(dx>=dy)
step=dx;
else
step=dy;
 
dx=dx/step;
dy=dy/step;
 
x=x1;
y=y1;
 
i=1;
while(i<=step)
{
putpixel(x,y,5);
x=x+dx;
y=y+dy;
i=i+1;
delay(100);
}
 
closegraph();
}

07/09/2021, 16:17 - Om Friend: #include<graphics.h>
#include<conio.h>
#include<math.h>
#include<dos.h>

 int main(){
  int gd = DETECT, gm;
  int x1, y1, x2, y2, dx, dy, steps, xinc, yinc, i;
  initgraph(&gd, &gm, "C:\\TC\\BGI ");
  printf("enter values of x1 and y1: ");
  scanf("%d %d", &x1, &y1);
  printf("enter values of x2 and y2: ");
  scanf("%d %d", &x2, &y2);

  dx = x2-x1;
  dy = y2-y1;
  if(abs(dx) > abs(dy)) {
    steps=abs(dx);
  }
  else {
    steps=abs(dy);
  }

  xinc=dx/steps;
  yinc=dy/steps;

  for(i = 0; i < steps; i++) {
    putpixel(x1, y1, 3);
    x1 = x1 + xinc;
    y1 = y1 + yinc;
  }

  getch();
  closegraph();
  return 0;
}

16/09/2021, 00:02 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>  
# include<conio.h>
#include<graphics.h>  
void drawline(int x0, int y0, int x1, int y1)  
{  
    int dx, dy, p, x, y;  
    dx=x1-x0;  
    dy=y1-y0;  
    x=x0;  
    y=y0;  
    p=2*dy-dx;  
    while(x<x1)  
    {  
        if(p>=0)  
        {  
            putpixel(x,y,WHITE); 
			delay(100); 
            y=y+1;  
            p=p+2*dy-2*dx;  
        }  
        else  
        {  
            putpixel(x,y,YELLOW); 
			delay(100); 
            p=p+2*dy;}  
            x=x+1;  
        }  
}  
int main()  
{  
    int gdriver=DETECT, gmode, error, x0, y0, x1, y1;  
    initgraph(&gdriver, &gmode, "c:\\turboc3\\bgi"); 
    printf("Enter First Coordinate : ");  
    scanf("%d %d", &x0, &y0);  
    printf("Enter Second Coordinate : ");  
    scanf("%d %d", &x1, &y1);  
    drawline(x0, y0, x1, y1);  
    closegraph();
	return 0;  
    
}

20/09/2021, 13:09 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h> 

#include<conio.h> 

struct studentInfo 

{	 

char name[50]; 

char address[100]; 

char email[50]; 

int age; 

int mobileNo; 

int marks; 

}; 

int main() 

{ 

studentInfo student[5];	 

int i; 

printf("Enter  student details:\n"); 

for (i = 0;i<5; i++) 

{ 

printf("\nEnter details for student # %d: \n", i+1); 

printf("Enter Name:"); 

scanf("%s",&student[i].name); 

printf("Enter Address:"); 

scanf("%s",&student[i].address); 

printf("Enter Email:"); 

scanf("%s",&student[i].email); 

printf("Enter Age:"); 

scanf("%d",&student[i].age); 

printf("Enter MobileNo:"); 

scanf("%d",&student[i].mobileNo); 

printf("Enter Marks:"); 

scanf("%d",&student[i].marks); 

} 

 

printf("\n\n\n Student details are as follows:\n"); 

for (i = 0;i<5; i++) 

{ 

printf("\n\nStudent # %d:", i+1); 

printf("\nName: %s",student[i].name); 

printf("\nAddress: %s",student[i].address); 

printf("\nEmail: %s",student[i].email); 

printf("\nAge: %d",student[i].age); 

printf("\nMobileNo: %d",student[i].mobileNo); 

printf("\nMarks: %d",student[i].marks); 

} 

 

return 0; 

}

20/09/2021, 19:25 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<graphics.h>
#include<conio.h>
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
int x0,y0,x1,y1,radius,dp;
int g_mode,g_driver=DETECT;
initgraph(&g_driver,&g_mode,"C:\TURBOC3\BGI");
printf("enter the co-ordinates=");
scanf("%d %d",&x1,&y1);
printf("enter the radius=");
scanf("%d",&radius);
x0=0;
y0=radius;
dp=1-radius;
do
{
putpixel(x1+x0,y1+y0,3);
putpixel(x1+y0,y1+x0,3);
putpixel(x1-y0,y1+x0,3);
putpixel(x1-x0,y1+y0,3);
putpixel(x1-x0,y1-y0,3);
putpixel(x1-y0,y1-x0,3);
putpixel(x1+y0,y1-x0,3);
putpixel(x1+x0,y1-y0,3);
delay(100);
if(dp<0){
dp+=(2*x0)+1;
}
else{
y0=y0-1;
dp+=(2*
x0)-(2*y0)+1;
}
x0=x0+1;
}while(y0>x0);
getch();
}

27/09/2021, 10:54 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#define Size 5
 
int top=-1, stack[Size];
void Push();
void Pop();
void show();

int main()
{
   
    int choice;
     
    while(1)    
    {
        printf("\ntransfer chairs from computer lab to seminar hall");
        printf("\n1.insert 4 chairs in the bunch\n2.remove the number of chairs from the bunch\n3.Show the number of chairs in the bunch\n4.End");
        printf("\n\nEnter the choice:");
        scanf("%d",&choice);
         
        switch(choice)
        {
            case 1: Push();
                    break;
           case 2: Pop();
                    break;
            case 3: show();
                    break;
            case 4: exit(0);
             
            default: printf("\nInvalid choice!!");
        }
    }
}

void Push()
{
    int x;
     
    if(top==Size-1)
    {
        printf("\nOverflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nEnter number of chairs to be inserted in a bunch:");
        scanf("%d",&x);
        top=top+1;
        stack[top]=x;
    }
}

void Pop()
{
    if(top==-1)
    {
        printf("\nUnderflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nPopped element:  %d",stack[top]);
        top=top-1;
    }
}

void show()
{
     
     
    if(top==-1)
    {
        printf("\nUnderflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nElements present in the stack: \n");
        for(int i=top;i>=0;--i)
            printf("%d\n",stack[i]);
    }
}

27/09/2021, 11:10 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#define size 5
#define MAX 5

int stack[size];

struct stack {
   int arr[MAX];
   int top;
};
 
void init_stk(struct stack *st) {
   st->top = -1;
}
 
void push(struct stack *st, int num) {
   if (st->top == size - 1) {
      printf("\nStack overflow(i.e., stack full).");
      return;
   }
   st->top++;
   st->arr[st->top] = num;
}
 
int pop(struct stack *st) {
   int num;
   if (st->top == -1) {
      printf("\nStack underflow(i.e., stack empty).");
      return NULL;
   }
   num = st->arr[st->top];
   st->top--;
   return num;
}
 
void display(struct stack *st) {
   int i;
   for (i = st->top; i >= 0; i--)
      printf("\n%d", st->arr[i]+5);
}
 
int main() {
   int element, opt, val;
   struct stack ptr;
   init_stk(&ptr);
   printf("\nTransfer chairs from computer lab to seminar hall");
   while (1) {
      printf("\n1.PUSH");
      printf("\n2.DISPLAY");
      printf("\n3.POP");
      printf("\n4.QUIT");
      printf("\n");
      printf("\nEnter your option : ");
      scanf("%d", &opt);
      switch (opt) {
      case 1:
           printf("\nInitially there are 5 Chair Present");
         printf("\nEnter number of chairs to be inserted in a bunch:");
         scanf("%d", &val);
         push(&ptr, val);
         break;
      case 2:
          printf("\nThe current stack elements are:");
         display(&ptr);
         break;      
      case 3:
         element = pop(&ptr);
         printf("\nThe element popped from stack is : %d", element);
         break;
      case 4:
         exit(0);
      default:
         printf("\nEnter correct option!Try again.");
      }
   }
   return (0);
}

04/10/2021, 10:05 - Om Friend: Ok
04/10/2021, 10:15 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<ctype.h>
 
#define MAX 50
 
typedef struct stack
{
    int data[MAX];
    int top;
}stack;
 
int precedence(char);
void init(stack *);
int empty(stack *);
int full(stack *);
int pop(stack *);
void push(stack *,int);
int top(stack );
void infix_to_postfix(char infix[],char postfix[]);

int main()
{
    char infix[50],postfix[50];
    printf("\nEnter an infix expression : ");
    gets(infix);
    infix_to_postfix(infix,postfix);
    printf("\nPostfix expression: %s",postfix);
}
 
void infix_to_postfix(char infix[],char postfix[])
{
    stack s;
    char x,token;
    int i,j;
    init(&s);
    j=0;
 
    for(i=0;infix[i]!='\0';i++)
    {
        token=infix[i];
        if(isalnum(token))
            postfix[j++]=token;
        else
            if(token=='(')
               push(&s,'(');
        else
            if(token==')')
                while((x=pop(&s))!='(')
                      postfix[j++]=x;
                else
                {
                    while(precedence(token)<=precedence(top(&s))&&!empty(&s))
                    {
                        x=pop(&s);
                        postfix[j++]=x;
                    }
                    push(&s,token);
                }
    }
 
    while(!empty(&s))
    {
        x=pop(&s);
        postfix[j++]=x;
    }
 
    postfix[j]='\0';
}
 
int precedence(char x)
{
    if(x=='(')
        return(0);
    if(x=='+'||x=='-')
        return(1);
    if(x==''x=='/'x=='%')
        return(2);
 
    return(3);
}
 
void init(stack *s)
{
    s->top=-1;
}
 
int empty(stack *s)
{
    if(s->top==-1)
        return(1);
 
    return(0);
}
 
int full(stack *s)
{
    if(s->top==MAX-1)
        return(1);
 
    return(0);
}
 
void push(stack *s,int x)
{
    s->top=s->top+1;
    s->data[s->top]=x;
}
 
int pop(stack *s)
{
    int x;
    x=s->data[s->top];
    s->top=s->top-1;
    return(x);
}
 
int top(stack *p)
{
    return (p->data[p->top]);
}
04/10/2021, 10:15 - Shivaraj Ghangale: infix to postfix
04/10/2021, 10:16 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#define Size 5
 
int top=-1, stack[Size];
void Push();
void Pop();
void show();

int main()
{
   
    int choice;
     
    while(1)    
    {
        printf("\ntransfer chairs from computer lab to seminar hall");
        printf("\n1.insert 4 chairs in the bunch\n2.remove the number of chairs from the bunch\n3.Show the number of chairs in the bunch\n4.End");
        printf("\n\nEnter the choice:");
        scanf("%d",&choice);
         
        switch(choice)
        {
            case 1: Push();
                    break;
           case 2: Pop();
                    break;
            case 3: show();
                    break;
            case 4: exit(0);
             
            default: printf("\nInvalid choice!!");
        }
    }
}

void Push()
{
    int x;
     
    if(top==Size-1)
    {
        printf("\nOverflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nEnter number of chairs to be inserted in a bunch:");
        scanf("%d",&x);
        top=top+1;
        stack[top]=x;
    }
}

void Pop()
{
    if(top==-1)
    {
        printf("\nUnderflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nPopped element:  %d",stack[top]);
        top=top-1;
    }
}

void show()
{
     
     
    if(top==-1)
    {
        printf("\nUnderflow!!");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("\nElements present in the stack: \n");
        for(int i=top;i>=0;--i)
            printf("%d\n",stack[i]);
    }
}

04/10/2021, 11:08 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>     
#include<ctype.h>    
# define MAX 50

typedef struct stk
{
int data[MAX];
int top;
}stk;


int precedence(char);
void init (stk *);
int empty (stk *);
int full (stk *);
int pop (stk *);
void push(stk *, int );
int top (stk *);
void infixToPostfix(char infix[], char postfix[]);


void main()
{

	char infix[30], postfix[30];
	printf("\n Enter an Infix expression");
	gets(infix);
	infixToPostfix(infix,postfix);                   /* call to convert */
	printf("Postfix Expression:%s ", postfix);
}

void infixToPostfix(char infix[], char postfix[])
{
	int i, j;		/* index for infix and postfix*/
	char token;
	char x;
	stk s;
	init(&s);
j=0;

for(i=0; infix[i]!='\0';i++)
{
	token=infix[i];
	if (isalnum(token))	/*check the character is alphanumeric or not*/
	 	postfix[j++]=token;
	else 
		if (token=='(')
		push(&s,'(');
		else
		if (token==')')
				  while((x=pop(&s))!='(')
		   postfix[j++]=x;
		else
		{
			while (precedence(token)<=precedence(top(&s)) && !empty(&s))
			{
				x= pop(&s);
postfix[j++]=x;
}
push(&s, token);
			}
	}


while (!empty(&s))
{
	x=pop(&s);
	postfix[j++]=x;
}

postfix[j]='\0';

}

int precedence(char x)
{
	if (x== '(')						return(0);
	if (x== '+' || x=='-')				return(1);
if (x== '*' || x=='/' || x=='%')		return(2);
return(3);

}



void init(stk *s)
{
	s->top= -1;
}


int empty (stk*s)
{	if (s->top==-1) 
return (1);
	return(0);
}


int full(stk*s)
{
	if (s-> top ==MAX-1)
		return(1);
	return(0);
}

void push(stk*s, int x)
{
	s->top= s->top+1;
	s->data[s->top]=x;
}


int pop (stk *s)
{	int x;
	x=s->data [s->top];
s->top=s->top - 1;
	return(x);
}

int top(stk *p)
{
	return (p->data[p->top]);
}

void reverse(char str[])
{
int len, i=0, j=0;
len=strlen(str);
j=len–1;
while(j>= 0)
{
if (str[j] == '(') temp[i] = ')';
else
if ( str[j] == ')') temp[i] = '(';
else temp[i] = str[j]; i++, j––;
}
temp[i] = '\0';
}
void InfixtoPostfix(char source[], char target[])
{
int i=0, j=0;
char temp;
strcpy(target,
"");
while(source[i]!= '\0')
{
if(source[i]=='(')
{
push(st, source[i]);
i++;
}
else
if(source[i] == ')')
{
while((top!=–1) && (st[top]!='('))
{ target[j] = pop(st); j++; }
if(top==–1)
{
printf("\n INCORRECT EXPRESSION");
exit(1);
}
temp = pop(st);
i++;
}
else
if(isdigit(source[i]) || isalpha(source[i]))
{ target[j] = source[i]; j++; i++; }
else if( source[i] == '+' || source[i] == '–' || source[i] == '*' ||
source[i] == '/' || source[i] == '%')
{
while( (top!=–1) && (st[top]!= '(') && (getPriority(st[top])
> getPriority(source[i])))
{ target[j] = pop(st); j++; }
push(st, source[i]); i++;
}
else
{ printf("\n INCORRECT ELEMENT IN EXPRESSION");
exit(1);
}
}
while((top!=–1) && (st[top]!='('))
{ target[j] = pop(st); j++; } target[j]='\0';
}
int getPriority( char op)
{
if(op=='/' || op == '*' || op=='%')
return 1;
else if(op=='+' || op=='–')
return 0;
}
void push(char st[], char val)
{
if(top==MAX–1)
printf("\n STACK OVERFLOW");
else
{ top++; st[top] = val; }
}
char pop(char st[])
{
char val=' ';
if(top==–1)
printf("\n STACK UNDERFLOW");
else
{ val=st[top]; top––;
}
return val;
}

void boundaryfill(int x,int y,int f_color,int b_color)
{
if(getpixel(x,y)!=b_color && getpixel(x,y)!=f_color)
{
putpixel(x,y,f_color);
boundaryfill(x+1,y,f_color,b_color);
boundaryfill(x,y+1,f_color,b_color);
boundaryfill(x-1,y,f_color,b_color);
boundaryfill(x,y-1,f_color,b_color);
}
}

void floodfill (int x,int y,int old,int newcol) 
{  
                int current;  
                current=getpixel(x,y);  
                if(current==old)  
                {  
                                delay(5);  
                                putpixel(x,y,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x+1,y,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x-1,y,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x,y+1,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x,y-1,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x+1,y+1,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x-1,y+1,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x+1,y-1,old,newcol);  
                                floodfill(x-1,y-1,old,newcol);  
                }  
}

}

18/10/2021, 10:22 - Shivaraj Ghangale: //implementation of queue
#include <stdio.h>
#define MAX 5

void insert();
void delete();
void display();
int queue_array[MAX];
int rear = - 1;
int front = - 1;
void main()
{
int choice;
do
   {
printf("\n1.Insert car in car washing center \n");
printf("2.deliver washed  car \n");
printf("3.total number of cars present  in center \n");
printf("4.exit \n");
printf("\nEnter your choice : ");
scanf("%d", &choice);
switch (choice)
  {
case 1:
insert();
break;
case 2:
delete();
break;

case 3:
display();
break;
case 4:printf("\nexit");
break;
default:
printf("\nWrong choice \n");
   
}
}
while (choice!=4);

}


void insert()
{
int add_item;
if (rear == MAX - 1)
printf("\nbooking is full \n");
else
{
if (front == - 1)
/*If queue is initially empty */
front = 0;
printf("\nno.of car to be insert  in carwashing center : ");
scanf("%d", &add_item);
rear = rear + 1;
queue_array[rear] = add_item;
}
}
void delete()
{
if (front == - 1 || front > rear)

{
printf("\nno cars present in carwashing center \n");
return ;
}
else
{
printf("\ndelivered car no.is : %d\n", queue_array[front]);
front = front + 1;
}
}
void display()
   {
int i;
if (front == - 1)
printf("\ncarwashing center is empty \n");
else
   {
printf("\ntotal cars present in carwashing center : \n");
for (i = front; i <= rear; i++)
printf("%d ", queue_array[i]);
printf("\n");
   }
   }

08/11/2021, 11:23 - Shivaraj Ghangale: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#define size 4
struct Node
{
  int data;
  struct Node *next;
};
typedef struct Node node;
node *head = NULL;

node *addNode()
{
  node *temp = malloc(sizeof(node));
  temp->next = NULL;
  return temp;
}
node *insertData(node *head, int value)
{

  node *temp;
  temp = addNode();
  temp->data = value;
  if (head == NULL)
    head = temp;
  else
 {
    node *p;
    p = head;
    while (p->next != NULL)
    {
      p = p->next;
    }
    p->next = temp;
  } 

return head;
}
node *insertAtBeginning(node *head, int value)
{
  node *temp = addNode();
  temp->data = value;
  temp->next = head;
  head = temp;
  return head;
}
 void insertAtEnd(node *head,int value)
{
  node *temp=addNode();
  node *last=head;
  temp->data=value;
  if(head==NULL){
    head=temp;
    return;
  }
while(last->next!=NULL){
    last=last->next;
  }
  last->next=temp;
  return;

}

void deleteFromEnd(node *head)
{
   node *temp= head;
   while(temp->next->next!=NULL){
     temp=temp->next;
   }
   temp->next=NULL;
 return;
}

void printList(node *head)
{
  node *temp = head;
  if (temp == NULL)
    printf("Nothing To Print:\n");
  else
  {
 printf("Printing list:\n");
    while (temp != NULL)
    {
      printf("%d->", temp->data);
      temp = temp->next;
    }
  }
}

int main(int argc, char const *argv[])
{
  int ch, value;

  while (1)
  {
    printf("\n1.Enter the student \n2.Display the list in linked manner\n3.Insert student at beginning\n4.Insert student at end\n5.Delete From End \n6.Quit\n");
printf("\nEnter your choice:");
    scanf("%d", &ch);

    switch (ch)
    {
    case 1:
 printf("Enter the student:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      head = insertData(head, value);

      break;
    case 2:
      printList(head);
      break;
    case 3:
      printf("Enter a student at Begginning:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      head = insertAtBeginning(head, value);
      break;
case 4:
      printf("Enter a student at End:");
      scanf("%d", &value);
      insertAtEnd(head,value);
      break;
     case 5:
     deleteFromEnd(head);
     break;
    case 0:
      return 0;
      break;
  default:
      break;
    }
  }

  //printf("%d",head);
  // printList(head);
  return 0;
}

15/11/2021, 11:26 - Om Friend: #include<stdlib.h>
#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>


typedef struct node
{
    int data;
    struct node *next;
    
}NODE;
NODE *top=NULL;

int push(int x)
{ 
    NODE *ptr ;
    ptr = (NODE *) malloc(sizeof(NODE));
    
    
    if(ptr==NULL){
    	printf("Stack is full");
       	return -1;
    }
    ptr->data=x;
    ptr->next=top;
    top=ptr;
    return 1;
    
}
int pop()
{
    int x,ptr;
    NODE *p;

    if(ptr==NULL){
    	printf("Stack is empty");
          return -1;
    }
    p=top;
    top=top->next;
    x=p->data;
    p->next=NULL;
    free(p);
    
    return x;
    
}
int peek()
{
    
    if(top==NULL)
    {
       return -1;
    }
    else{
    	return top->data;
    }
    
}
int empty()
{
    
    if(top==NULL)
    {
       return 1;
    }
    else{
    	return -1;
    }
    
}
int full()
{
    NODE *p;
    if(top==NULL)
    {
       return 1;
    }
    else{
    	return -1;
    }
    
}

void display()
{
    NODE *p;
    if(top==NULL)
    {
    	printf("linklist is empty\n");
    	return ;
    }
    p=top;
    while(p!=NULL)
    {
    	printf("%d\n",p->data);
    	p=p->next;
    }
}

int main()
{
	int option,x,res;
	do
	{
		printf("*Choose Option*\n");
		printf("1.Push \n");
		printf("2.Pop \n");
		printf("3.Peek \n");
		printf("4.Check Full \n");
		printf("5.Check Empty \n");
		printf("6.Display \n");
		printf("7.Exit \n");
		
		printf("Enter Your Option =");
		
		
		scanf("%d",&option);
		
		switch(option)
		{
			case 1:printf("Enter Element to Push \n");
			       scanf("%d",&x);
			       res=push(x);
			       if(res==1)
			       {
			       	printf("%d is Pushed\n",x);
			       }
			       else
			       {
			       	printf("push is failed, Stack is full\n");
			       }
			       break;
			case 2:res=pop();
			       if(res==-1)
			       {
			       	printf("pop is failed,stack is empty\n");
			       }
			       else
			       {
			       	printf("%d is popped\n",res);
			       }
			       break;
			case 3:res=peek();
			       if(res==-1)
			       {
			       	printf("peek is failed,stack is empty\n");
			       }
			       else
			       {
			       	printf("%d is at the top\n",res);
			       }
			       break;
			case 4:res=full();
			       if(res==1)
			       {
			       	printf("Stack is full\n");
			       }
			       else
			       {
			       	printf("Stack is not full\n");
			       }
			       break;
			case 5:res=empty();
			       if(res==1)
			       {
			       	printf("stack is empty\n");
			       }
			       else
			       {
			       	printf("Stack is Not Empty\n");
			       }
			       break;
			case 6:display();
			       break;
			case 7:break;
			
			default: printf("Invalid Option Entered\n");
			         break;
	          
		}         
	}
	while(option!=7);
}

15/11/2021, 15:32 - Shivaraj Ghangale: //WAP to implement the Koch Curve. 
#include<stdio.h> 
#include<graphics.h> 
#include<math.h> 
void koch(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, int i) 
{ 
	float angle = 60*M_PI/180; 
	int x3 = (2*x1+x2)/3; 
	int y3 = (2*y1+y2)/3; 
	int x4 = (x1+2*x2)/3; 
	int y4 = (y1+2*y2)/3; 
	int x = x3 + (x4-x3)*cos(angle)+(y4-y3)*sin(angle); 
	int y = y3 - (x4-x3)*sin(angle)+(y4-y3)*cos(angle); 
	if(i > 0) 
	{ 
	  	koch(x1, y1, x3, y3, i-1); 
	  	koch(x3, y3, x, y, i-1); 
	  	koch(x, y, x4, y4, i-1); 
	  	koch(x4, y4, x2, y2,i-1); 
	  	setcolor(6); 
	} 
	else 
	{ 
	  	line(x1, y1, x3, y3); 
	  	line(x3, y3, x, y); 
	  	line(x, y, x4, y4); 
	  	line(x4, y4, x2, y2); 
	} 
	delay(10); 
} 
int main() 
{ 
	int gd = DETECT, gm; 
	initgraph(&gd, &gm, "C:\\TC\\BGI"); 
	int x1 , y1  , x2 , y2 ; 
	printf("\nEnter the Value of x1 and y1 :"); 
	scanf("%d%d",&x1,&y1); 
	printf("\nEnter the Value of x2 and y2 :"); 
	scanf("%d%d",&x2,&y2); 
	koch(x1, y1, x2, y2, 4); 
	getch(); 
	return 0; 
}

void koch(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, int i) 
{ 
 float angle = 60*M_PI/180; 
 int x3 = (2*x1+x2)/3; 
 int y3 = (2*y1+y2)/3; 
 int x4 = (x1+2*x2)/3; 
 int y4 = (y1+2*y2)/3; 
 int x = x3 + (x4-x3)*cos(angle)+(y4-y3)*sin(angle); 
 int y = y3 - (x4-x3)*sin(angle)+(y4-y3)*cos(angle); 
 if(i > 0) 
 { 
  koch(x1, y1, x3, y3, i-1); 
  koch(x3, y3, x, y, i-1); 
  koch(x, y, x4, y4, i-1); 
  koch(x4, y4, x2, y2,i-1); 
  setcolor(6); 
 } 
 else 
 { 
  line(x1, y1, x3, y3); 
  line(x3, y3, x, y); 
  line(x, y, x4, y4); 
  line(x4, y4, x2, y2); 
 } 
 delay(10); 
}

15/11/2021, 16:20 - Om Friend: #include<stdio.h> 

#include<conio.h> 

#include<graphics.h> 

int main()  

{ 

int gd=DETECT,gm; 

initgraph(&gd,&gm,"C:\\TC\\BGI"); 

int x1,y1,x2,y2,xmax,xmin,ymax,ymin,xx1,yy1,xx2,yy2,dx,dy,i; 

int p[4],q[4]; 

float t1,t2,t[4]; 

printf("Enter the lower co-ordinates of window"); 

scanf("%d %d",&xmin,&ymin); 

printf("Enter the upper co-ordinates of window"); 

scanf("%d %d",&xmax,&ymax); 

setcolor(8); 

rectangle(xmin,ymin,xmax,ymax); 

printf("Enter x1 and y1 :"); 

scanf("%d%d",&x1,&y1); 

printf("Enter x2 and y2 :"); 

scanf("%d%d",&x2,&y2); 

line(x1,y1,x2,y2); 

dx=x2-x1; 

dy=y2-y1; 

p[0]=-dx; 

p[1]=dx; 

p[2]=-dy; 

p[3]=dy; 

q[0]=x1-xmin; 

q[1]=xmax-x1; 

q[2]=y1-ymin; 

q[3]=ymax-y1; 

for(i=0;i < 4;i++){  

if(p[i]!=0){ 

t[i]=(float)q[i]/p[i]; 

} 

else 

if(p[i]==0 && q[i] < 0) 

printf("line completely outside the window"); 

else 

if(p[i]==0 && q[i] >= 0) 

printf("line completely inside the window"); 

} 

if (t[0] > t[2]){ 

t1=t[0]; 

} 

else{ 

t1=t[2]; 

} 

if (t[1] < t[3]){ 

t2=t[1]; 

} 

else{ 

t2=t[3]; 

} 

if (t1 < t2){ 

xx1=x1+t1*dx; 

xx2=x1+t2*dx; 

yy1=y1+t1*dy; 

yy2=y1+t2*dy; 

printf("line after clipping:"); 

setcolor(3); 

line(xx1,yy1,xx2,yy2); 

} 

else{ 

printf("line lies out of the window"); 

} 

getch(); 

}
